# Design Specs — HTML Only (with UI Mockups)

When brainstorming, designing features, or writing specs under `docs/superpowers/specs/`:

## Do NOT create `.md` design specs

- **Never** write `docs/superpowers/specs/*.md` or `*-design.md`.
- If a Markdown spec already exists, convert it to HTML and delete the `.md` file in the same change set.
- Implementation **plans** in `docs/superpowers/plans/` may stay `.md` unless the user asks otherwise.

## Output format

Create a **single self-contained HTML file**:

```
docs/superpowers/specs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-design.html
```

Requirements:

- Valid HTML5, `lang="th"` when UI copy is Thai
- **Inline CSS** only (no external assets required to open the file)
- Openable by double-click in a browser
- Readable typography, tables, code blocks, and section cards

## Required sections

Every design spec HTML must include:

1. **Header** — title, date, owner, scope
2. **Goals / Non-goals**
3. **Current state**
4. **User workflow** (numbered steps)
5. **UI Details** — see below (mandatory)
6. **Data model / API** (when applicable)
7. **Error handling & test checklist**

## UI Details section (mandatory)

Include a dedicated `<section id="ui-details">` with **visual HTML mockups**, not prose-only descriptions.

For each screen, dialog, or major state:

- Build a **wireframe** using HTML + CSS (boxes, borders, placeholder inputs, badges, buttons)
- Label each mockup: screen name, route, and who can access it
- Show **key states** when relevant (empty, loading, error, locked, success)
- Use **real Thai UI copy** from the product (button labels, toasts, banners)
- Annotate behavior with short callouts beside or below the mockup

Example pattern:

```html
<section id="ui-details">
  <h2>UI Details</h2>
  <h3>หน้านับสินค้า — /tablet/count/[documentId]</h3>
  <div class="mockup">
    <div class="mockup-header">CNT-BKK1-20260311 · นับแล้ว 12/414</div>
    <div class="mockup-card mockup-locked">
      <span class="badge badge-amber">กำลังนับโดย สมชาย</span>
      ...
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="mockup-note">เมื่อ lock หมด 30 วินาที การ์ดกลับเป็นแก้ไขได้</p>
</section>
```

Add mockup CSS classes (`.mockup`, `.mockup-card`, `.badge`, `.mockup-note`) in the same file.

## Brainstorming / superpowers override

When `brainstorming` skill says to write `docs/superpowers/specs/*.md`, follow **this rule instead**: write `.html` with UI mockups, then ask the user to review the HTML file.

## Commit

After adding or updating a design spec HTML, commit and push per `commit-and-push` rule.
